cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for non-rigid image registration, which involves optimizing and learning spatial transformations between pairs of images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The method also involves maximizing an image-wise similarity metric, which involves optimization techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the proposed method is evaluated on 3D structural brain magnetic resonance images, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
